text: Privacy Policy - Elly Health Contact Privacy Policy Last Updated: April , â INTRODUCTION Elly Health , (âElly,â âwe,â âusâ) has created this privacy policy (âPrivacy Policyâ) in order to set out how we collect, use, and disclose personal information through our website located at (the âWebsiteâ) and our mobile app (the âAppâ) that is offered as part of the Elly Elly is a digital health solution which provides audio content to patients living with chronic This Privacy Policy applies to all of the products, services, and websites offered by Elly or our related, affiliated and or subsidiary companies (collectively the âServicesâ). The privacy of our customers is of great importance to By visiting our Website and or using the Services in any manner, you acknowledge that you accept the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy Policy and you hereby consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy The information on this site is not intended or implied to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis or All content, including text, graphics, images and information, contained on or available through this web site is for general information purposes Elly makes no representation and assumes no responsibility for the accuracy of information contained on or available through this web site, and such information is subject to change without You are encouraged to confirm any information obtained from or through this web site with other sources, and review all information regarding any medical condition or treatment with your physician . NEVER DISREGARD PROFESSIONAL MEDICAL ADVICE OR DELAY SEEKING MEDICAL TREATMENT BECAUSE OF SOMETHING YOU HAVE READ ON OR ACCESSED THROUGH THIS WEBSITE OR MOBILE â WHAT DOES THIS PRIVACY POLICY COVER? This Privacy Policy covers our collection, use and disclosure of information about identifiable individuals and information which can be used to identify an individual (âPersonal Informationâ). Personal Information does not include âaggregateâ information which we aggregate from information (including Personal Information) you provide to Personal Information may be collected about our customers, prospective customers, visitors to the Website, and end users of the You can choose not to provide us with certain information, but by doing so, you may not be able to take advantage of many of the features and functionality of our This Privacy Policy does not apply to the practices of companies that we do not own or You understand and agree that Elly and its authorized business partners, affiliates, subsidiaries or agents (collectively, âEllyâ, âusâ or âweâ) may collect, maintain, and process information provided by you, on and through the You represent and warrant that you have permission to share any information you elect to provide Elly, you consent to such information being shared with third parties, including, if applicable, healthcare providers, and that such information is accurate, current, , and consistent and relevant for the purpose for which you are providing â COLLECTION AND USE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION AND OTHER DATA Account Information: Â In order to use the Services, users may be required to have a valid Elly account to log in to the Website (an âAccountâ). When you register for the Services, Elly collects your name and email address (âAccount Informationâ). Elly will also have access to information about your use of the Services such as which audio content you listen to, how often you listen to content and other information available that is combined with your Account Once you create an account with us and sign in to our services, you are not anonymous to Elly collects Personal Information in the following general ways: â Elly collects Personal Information you knowingly choose to submit to us through the Services, such as your name and email â When you access or use the Services, Elly may automatically receive and record information on our server logs from your browser, including your IP address, cookies, and the pages you IP addresses are automatically reported by your browser each time you view a web Your IP address is stored by Elly when you register with â [If you link your Account to Appleâs HealthKit, FitBit, Google Health, or other third party account, Elly may collect the information you have stored in those accounts that are related to the services we Generally, Elly uses the Account Information (including Personal Information) to deliver the Services to you, to improve the delivery of our Services and related products and services, to conduct our business, to develop analytics and aggregated data that allow us to improve our Services and related products and services, or to correspond with Specifically, Elly uses Personal Information to: â Authenticate access to the Account and provide access to the Services â Provide, operate

About | Snorble® Skip to content Menu Home About About menu Inspiration Engineering Team Environment Preorder News FAQ Contact Us Facebook Twitter Pinterest Instagram YouTube Search again About Snorble® INSPIRATION ENGINEERING TEAM The Inspiration Behind Snorble Snorble is the brainchild of serial entrepreneur Mike Having gone through the motions of trying to establish a consistent and healthy bedtime routine for his own kids, Max & Emily, Mike realized there had to be something out there that could help with After Googling “How to get a toddler to sleep” and receiving million results, Mike discovered there were several sleep aids and trainers on the To his dismay, however, none of them seemed to have the holistic approach to bedtime that he was looking Convinced that his own son was, in Mike’s words, “an incredibly adorable descendant of Dracula and realizing that necessity truly was the mother of invention, Mike went ahead and invented The Engineering Behind Snorble Building the most advanced sleep trainer and magical bedtime experience turned out to be quite the It began with prototyping what Snorble should even look like and started with over concepts! That was only the beginning We soon realized that in order to build all of the features into Snorble, we were going to have to not only decide what our little buddy was going to look like, but how we were going to get him to speak, animate, monitor and provide both soothing lights and magical ceiling Oh yeah—did we mention the mobile app development too, so parents could customize the bedtime routine and receive reports on their child’s behaviors and habits? Nothing like this had ever been done In order to pull this off, Mike knew he had to assemble a team, and that’s exactly what he PhDs in artificial intelligence, child psychologists, animators, programmers who understood gamification, experts in product development, experienced business advisors and even a former Walt Disney Imagineer! We soon started exploring how everything would , function, and We looked at how colors and sounds affect We looked at the latest LED, audio and projection We researched what a toddler’s daily routine typically We just got as into Snorble as we possibly Perhaps most importantly though, we spoke to parents about what their pain points were in developing a nighttime routine—and how Snorble could address After nearly a year of intense and thoughtful research and development, we finally were able to bring Snorble to We think it’s more than a sleep trainer…we look at it as more of a partner for you and a companion for your child, and we’re not done You see, creativity is what drives our company and with that in mind, the Snorble ecosystem will always keep We have lots of exciting plans to explore down the road, from clothing lines, to smart toothbrushes, and even perhaps a children’s morning program starring our loveable Whatever we do though, understand that the one thing that continues to drive our development is you! We’ll always ask ourselves “how can we best serve parents and kids in a responsible, safe, and innovative way?” Hopefully we’ll keep surprising you with the right answers that keep coming to us from the magical world of Lullaboo… The Team Behind Snorble "We ve formed an amazing team with experts from across industries" Rizkalla, CEO and Mike Rizkalla, and CEO Doug Hughes, Thomas Chan, Tech Lead Brian Collins, Executive Creative Director Steve Hecker, Engineering and Mfg Lead Ryan Patey, Social Media Manager Dina Rizkalla, Operational Leader and Program Mgmt Monica Warren, Chief Educator - Early Childhood Expert Patrick Wesonga, Head of Experience Mike Rizkalla, and CEO An Creative Leader in the Technology Robotics industry with experience in organizations ranging from startup to $75M global businesses, with proven performance managing revenue goals up to $10M, operational budgets of up to $16M, and capital expense budgets of up to $2.5M. Logs, Reports and Other Information Practice portal and staff application RCP’s system is supported by a service portal that includes web login and also downloadable apps for iPhones, iPads, and Android Intuitive easy to Allows practice to set up new patients and monitor those enrolled in remote care management and chronic care management Ordering and Setting Up Patients Practice or other health care organization can easily enroll patients in the programs with 5 simple A care team is assigned to each patient and equipment is If the practice elects to stock equipment to support these programs, the patient can take them If not, RCP will ship the devices directly to the patient s Billing and information is also Equipment Inventory RCP can supply equipment directly to the practice or to the Equipment selections are based on capabilities, pricing, and integration with the RCP Devices are supported with encrypted communications and also integrated into the RCP portal for easy management by All reporting and alerts are cataloged by patients—so patients with multiple devices have their data integrated and instantly RCP Hub An essential component of the RCP solution set is the Hub that eliminates any need for patient Simply plug it in and it starts working, patients can take it with them for vacations or 2 nd homes and there are no changes The RCP Hub works on the cellular network and is automatically configured to integrate via Bluetooth to RCP This eliminates a huge issue with remote care management models: accessing patient phones, downloading apps, or logging devices into WiFi Reminders and Adherence Key to any program is ensuring patient adherence to generating data timely and RCP includes automated reminders via text or automated phone calls to The physician or care manager selects a time each day when measurements are expected to be collected: if the patient has not yet used the device, a text reminder is sent within a specified time frame, and if not responded to, or the patient does not use a cell phone, an automated call is If a patient is traveling, the patient can click on a link to enter their data if responding to a text or, using voice recognition, they can simply state their Patient Logs, Alerts, Alarms, Reports RCP offers a highly efficient user interface for staff to review patient It even collects time spent with each patient, and accounts for text and All patient data for remote care management and chronic care management is easy to read and presented both in summary graph format or detailed Physicians can also set up expected ranges for readings of various devices and those falling outside of those ranges can be either in alert or alarm Alert status patients are highlighted in a different color in the reports and moved to the top of most Alarms are more serious, and the RCP system will send texts or to designated care personnel assigned to that All is configurable per patient and Copyright , Remote Reach Home How it works Resources Blog Follow us on: Youtube Created with How It Works We believe that blockchains have not reached their full potential because no development environment provides these Therefore, developers must provide for them on their own, which is expensive and The Reach platform will enable tens of millions of developers to participate in the Blockchain community, rather than only the thousands that participate today, by drastically lowering the barrier to entry into blockchain and seriously raising the productivity of DApp Why 1 Traditional developers are not included in the blockchain movement Current blockchain development requires detailed knowledge of particular networks and cryptographic This knowledge is not pervasive among traditional Further, it is too expensive and risky to acquire because no blockchain platform is perceived as “safe” or 2 DApps involve many cooperating components to deploy successfully and The details of the smart contract, , and correctness proofs must all agree on every detail of the program from the protocol details (like data formats and method API) to the logical operations of the No existing DApp language allows all of these components to be specified at the same time or in a way that guarantees 3 DApps require a high standard of correctness because mistakes can automatically put great financial resources at risk (c.f. DAO hack). No existing DApp development environment incorporates formal verification of the distributed computation executed by the How The Reach platform provides these three services via a language (DSL) for specifying DApps and a specialized compiler that projects the specification into each of the output components while performing automatic verification of correctness Language We allow the developer to write and think at the level of business logic, rather than at the level of the intricate details of a blockchain Our DSL uses a subset of JavaScript to specify the entire DApp: the smart contract, the clients run on the , the servers run on the , and all communication between all the Since the entire specification is in a single language, we enable any developer to quickly create, reason about and deploy Blockchain Agnostic We output the DApp to a generalized backend language, and we then use “connectors” to translate the backend language to the correct byte code, while remaining faithful to the interfaces offered by actual This allows a developer to build on any blockchain platform that would best serve the Safety Guarantees We ensure that the DApp is free from errors without having to write tests of what the program should Instead, developers write down what their program must not do, and we ensure that these bad outcomes never The compiler uses , A transformation, security, and projection to derive each component correctly from the single The compiler is integrated with a (SMT) theorem prover (e.g. Z3) to automatically check the correctness of the application via predicates, as well as automatically generated properties appropriate for all Ready to make blockchain practical? There’s no way to effortlessly remember and recall the details about the relationships that could impact and even drive your Until Riley’s goal is to connect people to simpler times, when you knew everyone around you and you knew them You weren’t bombarded with noise everywhere you looked, you weren’t connected to seventeen thousand people across a dozen social We are on a mission to prevent the impending social crisis caused by being connected to everybody, but knowing Our singular goal is to increase the number of meaningful relationships you have in your professional Riley is the driven, relationships insights You can ask any question: Who’s son plays soccer? Who drinks Stags Leap? Who loves the Dodgers (do people really love the Dodgers)? And we’re here 7 for OUR LEADERSHIP Meet our ANDREW REINER NATHANIEL COHEN Andrew’s infatuation with entrepreneurship started when he was just —building a company that he grew to over clients and selling it before even enrolling in After graduating from Babson College he worked at Lehman Brothers & Barclays Capital in capital markets then was a quant jock at Hedge fund ($4.5b in AUM). Andrew is currently active mentor and advisor for a handful of startups and runs a ,000+ person community revolving around the startup He and his wife have two adorable boys, ages 3 and 1, was born and raised in Manhattan and is a huge New York Mets Nathaniel is an Engineer in communication systems (BSc & MSc) from EPFL (Switzerland)

Kurome Therapeutics menu Technology Team News Contact Subverting Cancer’s Ability to Evade Therapy Targeting Adapative Resistance Kurome Therapeutics is developing therapies that target cancer cells that have immune signaling pathways in order to avoid destruction by traditional therapeutic agents and subvert adaptive resistance Adaptive Resistance is Complex… Cancer cells adapt to and targeted therapies by signaling pathways previously thought to only be utilized by the host immune This is referred to as adaptive resistance This adaptive resistance mechanism allows the cancer cell to survive conventional chemotherapeutic and targeted therapies (e.g. FLT3 inhibitors) by activating IRAK1 and IRAK4 kinases …But Kurome Has a New Approach In trials, we have shown that inhibiting IRAK1 and IRAK4 provides an overall survival benefit in MDS and AML cells by suppressing this adaptive resistance mechanism in naïve and relapsed refractory cancer IRAK1 and IRAK4 are also in a variety of cancer cell backgrounds, where their inhibition suppresses the survival of the cancer cells Our Technology A targeted approach for treating hematological cancers and beyond These results were obtained in a xenograft (PDX) model from a patient whose tumor was positive for , D835Y, and This represents a prognostically unfavorable tumor that had also developed a resistance Kurome Therapeutics is a preclinical stage company that is developing a series of IRAK1 4, panFLT3 Preclinical studies have demonstrated: Broad range of efficacy in MDS and AML cell lines Synergy with Venclexta® (Venetoclax) automated the process of cooking, from start to His first burger robot prototype was the size of his dad’s Years later, he created the RoboBurger, the first burger robot the size of a vending machine Sign up for the beta See examples on GitHub Contact us for enterprise pricing Features How It Works Pricing Docs Blog Status Signup © Terms Privacy   Core concepts | Log In Sign Up Architect Core Concepts Before you get started with Architect, it is important to understand the four different entities that are used to describe and compose applications and Services Architect services can be thought of synonymously with microservices or in the use of the term in "Service-Oriented Architecture" (SOA) a service represents a discrete unit of functionality that can be updated independently of The standout feature of an Architect service is they include references to services they depend on in order to complete their All it takes to compose an Architect service is a config file that cites the service s Docker image and the service s Once a config file has been created, Architect can automate the deployment of its dependencies, instrument service discovery, and enforce strict network Components Architect components are collections of services designed to work exclusively All services encapsulated by a component are allocated In this way, components are a great structure for pairing services with private databases or other stateful Components are the main entity that get published to Architect s registry for use in multiple environments or by multiple In order to control ingress traffic, components can also be registered with unique interfaces that broker traffic to individual services within the This control not only allows upstream callers to connect to a component s APIs, but also allows for a variety of customizable rewrite rules that developers can use as a personalized API Since components can control these gateways and expose unique interfaces, components can also be cited as dependencies of other components allowing developers to collaborate more effectively across name : test component description : Sample Architect component # components can assert required parameters parameters : DB_USER : default : test description : Root username for the components database DB_PASS : required : true description : Root password for the components database DB_NAME : description : Name of the database housing the components state # components can cite other components as dependencies dependencies : test payments : latest # components can have N services Services are # private to the services : : image : postgres : environment : POSTGRES_USER : $ POSTGRES_PASSWORD : $ interfaces : postgres : port : protocol : postgres : image : test component : latest interfaces : main : environment : DB_ADDR : $ - $ DB_USER : $ DB_PASS : $ PAYMENTS_ADDR : $ dependencies [ test payments ] # components can control ingress traffic to their services with interfaces interfaces : public : description : Expose the API to upstream callers url : $ Platforms Architect platforms represent deploy targets – clusters or cloud provider accounts
